---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Stability Footwear Master Matrix | Practical Podiatrist">
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 text-slate-300 relative z-10">
    <header class="mb-12 border-b border-white/10 pb-8 text-center">
      <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent uppercase tracking-widest block mb-2">Biomechanical Footwear Guide</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white mb-4">The Stability Shoe Matrix</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">Why letting "comfort be your only guide" is a dangerous retail deception trap for failing feet.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>When dealing with acute structural damage like plantar fasciitis or collapsing arches, an ultra-soft, unsupportive shoe feels comfortable for five minutes in the store aisle but accelerates tissue tearing within weeks[cite: 2311, 2312, 2313]. True therapeutic comfort requires structural stiffness that holds your foot in a neutral position[cite: 2314].</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto border border-white/10 rounded-2xl bg-white/[0.02] backdrop-blur-xl shadow-2xl my-8">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-sm md:text-base">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-white font-semibold">
              <th class="p-4">Support Classification</th>
              <th class="p-4">Vetted Gold Standard Models</th>
              <th class="p-4">Mechanical Action</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-teal-400">Maximum Control Tanks</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-white">Brooks Addiction, Brooks Beast, Brooks Ariel</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-slate-400">Maximum torsional rigidity; stops severe calcaneal eversion and arch collapse[cite: 2293, 2294].</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-white/5">
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-blue-400">Premium Everyday Support</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-white">Hoka Arahi, Brooks Adrenaline, New Balance 860, Asics Gel-Kayano</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-slate-400">Consistent structured midfoot stabilization frames without excessive weight[cite: 2295, 2296].</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4 font-bold text-slate-400">Reliable / Value Stability</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-white">Asics GT-2000, Asics GT-1000, Mizuno Wave Inspire</td>
              <td class="p-4 text-slate-400">High-value pronation tracking adjustments[cite: 2297, 2298].</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-red-950/20 border border-red-500/20 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-red-400 block mb-1">🚨 The Minimalist Danger Warning</strong>
        <p>I explicitly advise patients to **NEVER wear Altra or zero-drop minimalist shoes** during an active inflammatory cycle[cite: 2275, 2279]. Flexible, flat designs stretch the Achilles tendon and plantar fascia to their absolute physical limits with every stride, worsening structural tearing[cite: 2280].</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
